      <item>
        <title>Run Jekyll on Windows</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;My blog didn’t get updated that often recently, huh?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Well, in addition to a big project I have been managing recently, I have less and less time to work on my Mac where all the development and publish to GitHub was set up. Thus, never got the chance to upload the couple of pages and changes I had on my Windows machine, ready to be Jekyll-built and pushed to GitHub.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That had to come to an end…&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have finally set up Jekyll on Windows and, believe it or not, it works like a charm. A big thank should go to the creator of this nice &lt;a href=&quot;http://jekyll-windows.juthilo.com/&quot;&gt;guide&lt;/a&gt;, which is, btw, a GitHub page!&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
